source('~/DanSav_STAT370/qscript.R')
x <- -10:10
y <- quad(x,b=2,c=3)
y2 <- quad(x,b=4,c=6)
y3 <- quad(x,b=0.5,c=3)
plot(x,y,'l')
lines(x,y2)
lines(x,y3)

# When a=0, the quadratic is linear

Case: b=0

source('~/DanSav_STAT370/qscript.R')
x <- -10:10
y <- quad(x,a=1,c=3)
y2 <- quad(x,a=2,c=4)
y3 <- quad(x,a=2.5,c=2)
plot(x,y,'l')
lines(x,y2)
lines(x,y3)

# When b=0, the quadratic is a parabola with y-intercept of c, and vertex on the vertical axis

Case: c=0

Case: a&b=0

source('~/DanSav_STAT370/qscript.R')
x <- -10:10
y <- quad(x,c=3)
y2 <- quad(x,c=2)
y3 <- quad(x,c=4)
plot(x,y,'l')
lines(x,y2)
lines(x,y3)

# When a and b = 0, the quadratic is a horizontal line where y = c.

Case: b&c=0

source('~/DanSav_STAT370/qscript.R')
x <- -10:10
y <- quad(x,a=1)
y2 <- quad(x,a=2)
y3 <- quad(x,a=3)
plot(x,y,'l')
lines(x,y2)
lines(x,y3)

# When b and c = 0, the quadratic is a parabola that gets thinner as a gets larger, with vertex at the origin.

Case: a&c=0

source('~/DanSav_STAT370/qscript.R')
x <- -10:10
y <- quad(x,b=1)
y2 <- quad(x,b=2)
y3 <- quad(x,b=4)
plot(x,y,'l')
lines(x,y2)
lines(x,y3)

# When a and c = 0, the quadratic is linear with slope of b, and y-intercept at the origin.
